07/26/2023,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/17/2023,08/03/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,A caregiver admitted to having an intense argument with their adult child in the presence of children in care.,"OP personnel submitted the following plan to ensure this does not happen in the future.
1. 2 hrs supervisor counsel on 7/27/2023 regarding his yelling at and in the presence of children. The counsel included minimum standards, agency policies, and best practices as it applies to dealing with traumatized children.
2. Central Texas Children's Home will be training regarding direct care discipline training and emotion management given to all staff over the next 3 months to include 5 hrs of TBRI training.
3. The OP personnel will increase the number of in-cottage monitoring spot checks (in-person and remote video camera) to be done no less than twice a month over the next six months.
4. Staff was issued a written reprimand on 7/28/2023 for yelling at the children and the use of profanity. A next-time offense could result in employment termination."
